</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kirle>Kirle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 289<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/7/02 11:08:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4356.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: weapon upgrade</span><hr size=1> I'm probably not going ot be much help here but your kinda sunk.  Just save your Copper till you can buy a Frostbringer then use the Lammy frostbringer till you see the next weapon you want and play from there, I've been using a Guard Gaptains Mallet, and a Frostbringer now for my last 4 lvls (Real life translation 10 months) and i've never had a serious problem with not being able to keep the mob on me.  I gennerally play with way better geared Rogues and monks who can take aggro from me at the drop of a hat. <p>Kirle Koward<br>
56 Ale-Slinging Warrior<br>
<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=quirtevans>QuirtEvans</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/8/02 4:29:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4356.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Some Ideas</span><hr size=1> One thing you could get for your offhand is the goranga spiked club, which rots all the time in Maiden's Eye.  12 23, I think, and it's free and easy to get, you can just wait in ME and watch the oocs (watch out for trains though, ME is notorious for those).<br>
<br>
You might also think about a club of the ice ocean for your offhand, I think it's 14 27 with a 149 DD proc.  They're pretty cheap these days, somewhere between 1K and 1500 on Saryrn, because of the recommended level (51) and the fact that there is better gear out there.  <br>
<br>
The top warrior in our guild has been using a 2HS lately, the weighty polearm, it drops somewhere in PoP and it must be very common because I've seen them for sale all the time, for as cheap as 1K.  29 34, with some other stats and a recommended level of 50.<br>
<br>
Tae Ew war mauls are pretty cheap too (I got one for 500, but that was a steal), 2HB, 33 36, with 65 HP and a couple of small saves, recommended level of 51.<br>
<br>
The easiest way to get new weaponry in the 50s is to take a healer and go to Rathe and kill HGs.  You could easily afford a new 1K weapon in a few hours, unless Rathe is crazy busy and you can't get any pulls.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=demolishionglobal>Demolishion global</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/8/02 8:10:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4356.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Some Ideas</span><hr size=1> Unfortunatly the Gorgana spiked club which Quirt is talking about is Primary slot only.  Still an ok weapon thou you may want to keep the lammy since it's a quicker poke.<br>
<br>
I have to agree with the gent saying he's using Captain's mallot + frosty and  keeping taunt.  That's a great 50-58 combo.  I currently use Defiance+Frosty and my DPS is a little less than the captain's mallot combo.  I usually dont have any problems keeping agro from uber rogues an such.  HOWEVER it's probably because i was a bard in another life with the way i spam my hotkeys ( Disarm, Bash, taunt, Bash, Taunt, Disarm,  rinse + repeat never miss a beat)<br>
<br>
If your budget is tight and a Frosty's out of the question, you could always go for:<br>
-- Veno axe -  11/24 10ac  procs an 85pt disease(or is it poison?) based DD  -- on povar usualy 1-1.5k<br>
--Snare Whip  14/28  procing u guessed it snare  -- povar 500-1k<br>
<br>
my advice is to save up for a frosty, or if your on friendly terms with the giants of Kael - get into as many dragon hunts as possible to have a chance at the head needed to actually quest the Frosty <p>My Gear --<br>
